<seg id="2989">This documentation is based on & kuser; 1.0. with this program you can manage the users and groups of your system.</seg>
<seg id="2990">To start with & kuser; it is sufficient to read the chapter Adaptation by & kuser; to read.</seg>
<seg id="2991">After you have made changes, you need to save it. either use the corresponding icon of the toolbar or the Save in the File menu.</seg>
<seg id="2992">& kuser; is a simple application. the main window consists of two card cards, user and user group list. to edit, select the desired user or group with double click on the entry. it appears the user or group properties dialog.</seg>
<seg id="2993">Some card cards are only displayed if you have advanced system settings. only if you have limited space restrictions (quota) for users, a card card will be created where you can configure individual settings. other cards appear if Shadow passwords are installed, for example / etc / master.passwd as in BSD installations.</seg>
<seg id="2994">The password management board appears if Shadow passwords are installed, for example / etc / master.passwd as in BSD installations.</seg>
<seg id="2995">This card card only appears if for at least a built-in filesystem space restriction (quota) is activated and initialized (recognizable at the file quota.user / quota.group on the file system). here, parameters can be changed for each user, with the restriction entries in KB are:</seg>
<seg id="2996">These parameters can be individually set for each filesystem. the current file system is selected with the help of the field file system with space restriction.</seg>
<seg id="2997">The tab group provides information about the group affiliations of the selected user. the standard group to which the user belongs can be found in the Primary Group. furthermore, the user can become a member in other groups by marking them in the large field.</seg>
<seg id="2998">The dialog properties of the group contains a list of all users. to add a user to the group, select this user in the list.</seg>
<seg id="2999">To add a user or group, select Add from the User or Group menu or click the appropriate Add button of the toolbar. editing or deleting the selected user or group works analog.</seg>
